
## 📌 Project Overview

Today’s KodeKloud DevOps challenge focused on one of the most common collaboration workflows in Git—**forking a repository**.

Forking creates a personal copy of another user's repository under your own account. This allows developers to experiment, develop features independently, 
and contribute back to the original project through Pull Requests without affecting the source repository.

In this lab, I logged into a self-hosted **Gitea** Git server as a newly onboarded developer and forked an existing project into my own workspace.

---

