## 📚 Key Takeaways

Forking is a fundamental Git workflow used across nearly every open-source project. By working from a personal fork, developers can safely implement changes, test new ideas, and submit contributions without directly modifying the original repository.

This lab reinforced how Git platforms like Gitea simplify collaborative software development.

